1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
Every content team knows the math. A finished minute of short-form video costs hours of people.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:14,941
A scripter, a voice session, an editor cutting b-roll, a captioning pass. Four hand-offs before anything ships.

3
00:00:14,941 --> 00:00:20,941
This short is the counter-argument. It was produced by a pipeline from one plain-text script.

4
00:00:20,941 --> 00:00:26,941
The narration you are hearing was generated through the ElevenLabs text to speech API.

5
00:00:26,941 --> 00:00:33,941
The score under it came from Eleven Music. The accents came from the sound effects API.

6
00:00:33,941 --> 00:00:40,941
Every API call lands in a run manifest with its model, its latency, and its cost in dollars.

7
00:00:40,941 --> 00:00:47,941
So when a customer asks what a finished minute costs, the answer is a receipt, not a guess.

8
00:00:47,941 --> 00:00:54,941
The stages that need a human keep a human. Script approval, brand sign-off, and the final quality pass.

9
00:00:54,941 --> 00:01:00,941
One operator, one command, one costed cut. That is the whole pitch.

